The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Ruling on study loan
                                                                                                               Ruling on study loan
                            
	Madurai, Aug. 11 (PTI): A Madras High Court bench today held that a second education loan for a member of the same family could be given only according to RBI guidelines and the loan applicant should satisfy the conditions.        
	The ruling was given while disposing of a writ petition filed by an applicant who had sought Rs 7.5 lakh as education loan from Punjab National Banks Kanyakumari Branch.        
	The petitioner should approach the bank with necessary documents, including personal guarantee given by the parents and equal security of tangible property to the satisfaction of the bank, the court said.                                                                                                                                                                            
